      • setAuthenticate

        public void setAuthenticate(boolean authenticate)
        This property should be set to true when the product is released because setting this property to false will make this app vulnerable to a Man-In-The-Middle attack. It is sometimes useful to set this property to false during development so that a self-signed certificate can be used by the server until an official certificate can be requested from a CA.
        Parameters:
        authenticate - Whether or not authentication will be performed on the server's certificate.

      • getUseHTTPS
